 studio system and changing conceptions of stardom, considering such Hollywood icons as Elizabeth Taylor and Paul Newman alongside such hallmarks of youth culture as Mia Farrow and Dustin Hoffman. Others, like Sidney Poitier and Peter Sellers, took advantage of the developing independent and international film markets to craft truly groundbreaking screen personae. And some were simply "famous for being famous," with celebrities like Zsa Zsa Gabor and Edie Sedgwick paving the way for today's reality stars.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aMotion picture actors and actressesvBiography. 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aAbramson, Leslie1 aBaron, Cynthia1 aBecker, Christine1 aBingham, Dennis1 aConway, Kelley1 aDoty, Alexander1 aKnight, Arthur1 aNewton, Darrell1 aPecknold, Diane1 aSieving, Christopher1 aSmith-Rowsey, Daniel1 aWojcik, Pamela Robertson, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813552293423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813552293.jpg  a978-3-11-068861-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK